Bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles. When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{2} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{}.

> TIP: Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over high heat. Add the @British pork mince{480%g} and sprinkle on the @Thai style spice mix{1}(sprinkled) (be careful it's spicy! Add less if you're not a fan of heat). Cook until browned, breaking it up with a #wooden spoon{} as it cooks, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Whilst the pork is cooking, halve the @green pepper{2}(halved and deseeded) and remove the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @spring onion{2}(trimmed and sliced thinly) then slice thinly. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Halve the @lime{1}. Once browned, add the green pepper to the pork and cook until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}, stir every couple of mins.

Mix the @ketjap manis{100%ml} with the @rice vinegar{30%ml} and @honey{30%ml} together in a #bowl{}. Squeeze in the lime juice. Once the pepper has softened, add the spring onions to the pan and pour the sauce onto the pork. Bring to a simmer. Bubble for ~{2%minutes}.

Stir half of the coriander into the pork mixture. Transfer 2 portions of the pork mixture to a bowl and set aside to cool (this will be for your lunch). Drain the noodles and add them to the pork mixture in the #pan{}, stir to coat. Cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Share the noodles between your bowls and finish with a sprinkle of remaining coriander. Enjoy!

When you've finished your dinner and the pork in the bowl has cooled, squeeze the @Coconut Chilli Lemongrass Steamed Basmati Rice{1}(pouch) to break up the rice and divide between your #lunch containers{}. Divide the reserved pork mixture between each container and top with the @salted peanuts{25%g}. Refrigerate and enjoy reheated in the #microwave{} until piping hot or straight from the fridge.